06348nam a22009495i 9783035618785DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20202020sz     fo  d z      eng d  a2019955719  a97830356187857 a10.1515/97830356187852doi  a(DE-B1597)531902  a(OCoLC)1154534485  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 4aNA2500 7aARC0130002bisacsh04a720.12231 aSarnitz, August, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aRelations in Architecture :bWritings and Buildings /cAugust Sarnitz. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (240 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tDedication -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- tNew Historiography and Big Data History -- tSocial Housing -- tBoundless Urbanism: Modern and Postmodern Situations -- tTransformations -- tThe Fiction of Space: On projection differences: Spatial envelope, spatial plan, spatial form, plan libre, white cube, dark room, art space -- tCase Study: The Private House -- tFour Approaches from Vienna: Josef Frank, Friedrich Kiesler, Hans Hollein, Wolf D. Prix -- tFurniture and Installations -- tEmigration – The Loss of Everyday Life: Ernst Lichtblau and Ernst A. Plischke -- tArchitectural Photography – And an Album of Photographs -- tBiography -- tIndex -- tList of Illustrations -- tImprint0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDer Titel des Buches setzt die beiden Tätigkeitsfelder, das Bauen und das Schreiben, des Architekten, Architekturhistorikers und Theoretikers August Sarnitz in eine wechselseitige Beziehung: im Schreiben entsteht der Kontext zum Gebauten – so wie das Bauen im Kontext des Geschriebenen steht. Eben diesem Wechselspiel folgt auch der Aufbau des Buches: einem Essay über Architekturgeschichte und Big Data folgen drei Aufsätze zu den Themen Städtebau, sozialem Wohnbau und der Fiktion des Raums. Auch einige prägende Wiener Architekten treten auf: Frank, Kiesler, Hollein und Prix. Die Themen Wohnen, Design und Möbel werden mit eigenen Projekten von Sarnitz illustriert; am Ende widmet sich das Buch der Architekturfotografie, die für Sarnitz als Publizisten große Bedeutung hat.  aThe title of the book sets the two fields of activity pursued by the architect, architectural historian and theorist August Sarnitz – building and writing – in a reciprocal relation: the context to what has been built emerges in the process of writing, just as the context to what has been written emerges in the process of building. The structure of the book follows precisely this reciprocity: an essay about architectural history and Big Data is followed by three on the topics of urban development, social housing, and the fiction of space. A number of influential Viennese architects appear as well: Frank, Kiesler, Hollein and Prix. The topics of housing, design and furniture are all illustrated with Sarnitz’s own projects; the end of the book is dedicated to architectural photography, which is especially important to Sarnitz in his capacity as publicist. The richly illustrated book is the first to document Sarnitz’s work as author, designer, exhibition designer, architect and photographer.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArchitectural design. 0aArchitecturexPhilosophy. 4aArchitectural Photography. 4aArchtiectural Theory. 4aHousing. 4aInterieur. 4aUrbanism. 7aARCHITECTURE / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertArt and Architecture eBook-Package 2020z978311073823008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBo